Since $94 = 4 + 5x$ for some $x \in \mathbb{N}$, my claim is that the first player wins when it chooses $4$ in the beginning. Then, whenever the second player choose $a, x \in\set{1, 2, 3, 4}$, the first player just add it to 5. So choose $5-a$. By doing this, the first player always reaches $10x + 9$ or $10x + 4$ for $x \in \mathbb{N}$.
